HEADWORD: Dorsiventral
<hw>Dor`si*ven"tral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Dorsum</ets> + <ets>ventral</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having distinct upper and lower surfaces, as
most common leaves. The leaves of the iris are not
<xex>dorsiventral</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>See
